Epigyne (
Fig. 1
). Lateral lobes surround a small u-shaped median field centrally located on the epigynal plate; lateral lobes fused before reaching posterior margin of median field.

Vulva (
Fig. 2
). One large copulatory opening that branches posterolaterally into short copulatory ducts that lead to laterally-located ovoid spermathecae; fertilisation ducts located posteriorly, directed posterolaterally; posterodorsal fold absent.

